news.title: Telangana HC orders eviction of encroachments for Musi riverfront project
news.para: In a recent order, the court issued several directions while disposing of a batch of writ petitions challenging the action of the government wings of making efforts to demolish residential houses.

news.title: Pending home sales in USA rise 2% in October 2024
news.para: The National Association of Realtors (NAR) said on Wednesday its Pending Home Sales Index, based on signed contracts, rose 2.0% last month to 77.4 - the highest since March - from 75.9 in September.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt proposes new policy to fast track bulk land allotment
news.para: The move is linked to the state's decision to come up with Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) Policy-2023 and the Incentive Policy for Fortune-500 Companies' Investments 2023 in place.

news.title: MCD imposes Rs 95.35 lakh fine for illegal dumping C&D waste in October 2024
news.para: The NGT sought regular replies from the authorities concerned with steps preventing air pollution in the national capital.

news.title: Gujarat: Swastika Overseas defrauded of 2.38 crore by importer and shipping sub-agent
news.para: Kapil Goriya, who runs Swastika Overseas, a Morbi-based ceramics trading company, travelled to Dubai to confront the importer but to no avail. He filed a complaint at B Division police station in Morbi in June.

news.title: Kolkata's first metro link to airport set to be ready by March 2025
news.para: The Noapara-Airport is the Phase I of Yellow Line, which will eventually link Barasat with Kolkata.

news.title: Delhi LG directs DDA to organise camps to resolve PM-UDAY applications
news.para: Delhi Lieutenant Governor VK Saxena on Wednesday directed Delhi Development Authority (DDA) to organize single window clearance camps to dispose of Prime Minister-Unauthorised Colonies in Delhi Awas Adhikar Yojna (PM-UDAY) applications.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP urges telecom operators to clear property tax dues
news.para: According to BBMP sources, there are nearly 10,000 telecom towers in the city and property tax towards many of them haven't been paid since Jan 9, 2015. The Palike estimates the dues amount to over Rs 100 crore.

news.title: Cachar administration directs brick kilns to adopt modern technologies to cut emissions
news.para: At a Wednesday meeting with brick kiln owners, district commissioner Mridul Yadav highlighted the importance of balancing economic progress with environmental protection.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance declares Agora City Centre stressed asset
news.para: The project has been mired in a series of controversies despite being among the most luxurious real estate projects built on a large scale in the city.

news.title: Malls may cut multiplex space as cinema-led revenues shrink
news.para: Mall developers are reducing multiplex spaces in future projects due to declining footfall and revenues.  Multiplexes now contribute only 6-7% of mall traffic, compared to 10% previously.  The rise of OTT platforms and a lack of compelling content are cited as key reasons, prompting developers to allocate more space to other entertainment and F&B options.

news.title: Godrej Properties launches QIP to raise up to Rs 6,000 crore
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Godrej Properties informed that the QIP Placement Committee authorized the opening of the issue on November 27, 2024.

news.title: Noida authority to acquire 25 hectares of land for industrial zone in sector 165
news.para: Land for the same will be bought from farmers through mutual consent, which officials noted is a collaborative approach to ensure smooth proceedings.

news.title: NHB probe uncovers inflated investments in Aviom India Housing Finance
news.para: The NHB investigation showed that "the statement of accounts of mutual fund(s) appear to be managed", the company informed lenders, said people cited above. The investment in mutual funds is much lower than Rs 115 crore disclosed to their auditors, the people said.

news.title: Flat buyers cannot be put at a disadvantage over builder's default: Bombay HC
news.para: Bandra's ALJ Residency Cooperative Housing Society (CHS) Ltd petitioned the high court in 2018 against the order of a deputy registrar of cooperative societies who had rejected its plea for a unilateral deemed conveyance certificate.

news.title: Mumbai: Over 60,000 Dharavi structures surveyed for redevelopment
news.para: "Over 50 teams work daily across Dharavi's five sectors and 34 zones," said a senior DRP-Slum Rehabilitation Authority official. "Each day, 300-400 tenements are numbered and 200-250 homes verified."

news.title: TVS Industrial & Logistics Parks expands into eastern India with new facility in Siliguri
news.para: ​​The 1.40 lakh sq ft facility, built on a 5.66-acre plot in Fulbari, marks TVS ILP's entry into the eastern Indian market and solidifies its position as a pioneer in delivering grade A industrial infrastructure, the company said without disclosing the value of the acquisition.

news.title: Paradigm Realty repays Rs 175 crore to Edelweiss Financial Services
news.para: The debt initially raised two years ago to fund the residential phase of 102 Downtown, a 10-acre mixed-use township in Oshiwara, Andheri West.

news.title: Trichy police crackdown on illegal sand mining in Kollidam riverbed
news.para: Following a tip-off, a police team was conducting surveillance in the Kollidam riverbed area near burial ground in Appathurai.

news.title: Prologis, RMZ Group to develop 30 acre logistic park in Bengaluru
news.para: The facility at Hoskote, a key logistics hub in Bengaluru, will span 30 acres, and it will initially deliver 500,000 sq ft, targeting third-party logistics and industrial clients.
